\end_layout

\end_inset

, denoted as 
\begin_inset Formula $\grad{\vec{u}}$
\end_inset

, is defined as such a quantity that satisfies
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\dd{\vec{u}}=\dd{\vec{x}}\cdot\left(\grad{\vec{u}}\right)
\]

\end_inset

It can be proved to be
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\grad{\vec{u}}=\left(\vec{e}_{i}\pdv{x_{i}}\right)\otimes\left(\vec{e}_{k}u_{k}\right)=\left(\vec{e}_{i}\otimes\vec{e}_{k}\right)\pdv{u_{k}}{x_{i}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Like any other rank-
\begin_inset Formula $2$
\end_inset

 tensor, it can be decomposed as a symmetric component 
\begin_inset Formula $\Tensor{E}:=\left(\vec{e}_{i}\otimes\vec{e}_{k}\right)E_{ik}$
\end_inset

, called the 
\noun on
strain rate tensor
\noun default

\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
tensor!strain rate ~
\end_layout

\end_inset

, plus an anti-symmetric component 
\begin_inset Formula $\Tensor{\Omega}:=\left(\vec{e}_{i}\otimes\vec{e}_{k}\right)\Omega_{ik}$
\end_inset

, called the 
\noun on
angular velocity tensor
\noun default

\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
tensor!angular velocity ~
\end_layout

\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\pdv{u_{k}}{x_{i}}=\underbrace{\frac{1}{2}\left(\pdv{u_{k}}{x_{i}}+\pdv{u_{i}}{x_{k}}\right)}_{E_{ik}}+\underbrace{\frac{1}{2}\left(\pdv{u_{k}}{x_{i}}-\pdv{u_{i}}{x_{k}}\right)}_{\Omega_{ik}}
\]

\end_inset

or equivalently
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\grad{\vec{u}}=\Tensor{E}+\Tensor{\Omega}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

