\begin_layout Standard
In 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}^{3}$
\end_inset

, the angular velocity tensor 
\begin_inset Formula $\Tensor{\Omega}$
\end_inset

 has only 3 independent components, since it is anti-symmetric (
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega_{ik}=-\Omega_{ki}$
\end_inset

):
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\Tensor{\Omega}=\begin{bmatrix}\vec{e}_{1} & \vec{e}_{2} & \vec{e}_{3}\end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix}0 & \Omega_{12} & -\Omega_{31}\\
-\Omega_{12} & 0 & \Omega_{23}\\
\Omega_{31} & -\Omega_{23} & 0
\end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix}\vec{e}_{1}\\
\vec{e}_{2}\\
\vec{e}_{3}
\end{bmatrix}
\]

\end_inset

Define
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\vec{\Omega}:=\sum_{i=1}^{3}\vec{e}_{i}\Omega_{i}\qquad\begin{bmatrix}\Omega_{1}\\
\Omega_{2}\\
\Omega_{3}
\end{bmatrix}=\begin{bmatrix}\Omega_{23}\\
\Omega_{31}\\
\Omega_{12}
\end{bmatrix}\iff\Omega_{i}\epsilon_{ijk}=\Omega_{jk}
\]

\end_inset

which can be proved to be a pseudo-vector
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
vector!pseudo-~
\end_layout

\end_inset

, called the 
\noun on
angular velocity vector
\noun default

\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
vector!angular velocity ~
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 The name is appropriate since it is analogous to the angular velocity vector
 of a rigid body:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\dd{\vec{x}}\cdot\Tensor{\Omega}=\dd{x_{j}}\Omega_{jk}\vec{e}_{k}=\dd{x_{j}}\left(\Omega_{i}\epsilon_{ijk}\right)\vec{e}_{k}=\underbrace{\vec{e}_{i}\times\vec{e}_{j}}_{\epsilon_{ijk}\vec{e}_{k}}\Omega_{i}\dd{x_{j}}=\vec{\Omega}\times\dd{\vec{x}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The angular velocity vector 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{\Omega}$
\end_inset

 is exactly one half of the 
\noun on
vorticity
\noun default
 (
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{\omega}:=\curl{\vec{u}}$
\end_inset

) at the same point:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\vec{\Omega}=\frac{\vec{\omega}}{2}
\]

\end_inset


