\begin_layout Standard
Generally, physical laws are stated on material bodies.
 In this section, we denote a material body as 
\begin_inset Formula $V^{m}$
\end_inset

 (
\begin_inset Formula $^{m}$
\end_inset

 stands for 
\bar under
m
\bar default
aterial body) to distinguish it from a general control volume 
\begin_inset Formula $V^{c}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition
The 
\noun on
material derivative
\noun default
 of an integral
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
derivative!material ~!~ of an integral
\end_layout

\end_inset

 taken on 
\begin_inset Formula $V^{c}$
\end_inset

 is defined to be the rate of change of the integral taken on the 
\begin_inset Formula $V^{m}$
\end_inset

 occupying 
\begin_inset Formula $V^{c}$
\end_inset

 at the same time, i.e.
\begin_inset CommandInset nomenclature
LatexCommand nomenclature
symbol "$\\DDt{}$"
description "material derivative"
literal "true"

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\boxed{\DDt{}\int_{V^{c}}\phi\dd{V}:=\dv{t}\int_{V^{m}}\phi\dd{V}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Corollary
For any CV:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\boxed{\begin{aligned}\DDt{}\int_{V^{c}}\phi\dd{V} & =\int_{V^{c}}\pdv{\phi}{t}\dd{V}+\oint_{\partial V^{c}}\vec{n}\cdot\vec{u}\phi\dd{S}\\
 & =\dv{t}\int_{V^{c}}\phi\dd{V}+\oint_{\partial V^{c}}\vec{n}\cdot\left(\vec{u}-\vec{u}^{c}\right)\phi\dd{S}
\end{aligned}
}\label{eq:DDtOnControlVolume}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Apply Reynolds transport theorem 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:ReynoldsTransportTheorem"

\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $\dv{t}\int_{V^{m}}\phi\dd{V}$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\dv{t}\int_{V^{m}}\phi\dd{V}=\int_{V^{m}}\pdv{\phi}{t}\dd{V}+\oint_{\partial V^{m}}\vec{n}\cdot\vec{u}^{m}\phi\dd{S}\label{eq:ReynoldsTransportTheoremOnMaterialBody}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

By definition, 
\begin_inset Formula $V^{m}$
\end_inset

 coincides with 
\begin_inset Formula $V^{c}$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{u}^{m}=\vec{u}$
\end_inset

 on 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial V^{m}$
\end_inset

, there are
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{aligned}\int_{V^{m}}\pdv{\phi}{t}\dd{V} & =\int_{V^{c}}\pdv{\phi}{t}\dd{V}\\
\oint_{\partial V^{m}}\vec{n}\cdot\vec{u}^{m}\phi\dd{S} & =\oint_{\partial V^{m}}\vec{n}\cdot\vec{u}\phi\dd{S}=\oint_{\partial V^{c}}\vec{n}\cdot\vec{u}\phi\dd{S}
\end{aligned}
\]

\end_inset

Inserting them into the RHS of 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:ReynoldsTransportTheoremOnMaterialBody"

\end_inset

 leads to the 1st line of 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:DDtOnControlVolume"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
The 2nd line of 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:DDtOnControlVolume"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 comes immediately by substituting 
\begin_inset Formula $\int_{V^{c}}\pdv{\phi}{t}\dd{V}$
\end_inset

 in the 1st line with
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\int_{V^{c}}\pdv{\phi}{t}\dd{V}=\dv{t}\int_{V^{c}}\phi\dd{V}-\oint_{\partial V^{c}}\vec{n}\cdot\vec{u}\phi\dd{S}
\]

\end_inset

which comes from Reynolds transport theorem 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:ReynoldsTransportTheorem"

\end_inset

, too.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
物质点上的物质导数
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{u}\phi\in C^{1}(V)$
\end_inset

, then Gauss's divergence theorem can be applied to the surface integral
 in the first line of 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:DDtOnControlVolume"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, which leads to
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\DDt{}\int_{V}\phi\dd{V}=\int_{V}\left(\pdv{\phi}{t}+\div(\vec{u}\phi)\right)\dd{V}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Apply the mean value theorem on both sides, we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\DDt{\ev{\phi}\abs{V}}=\ev{\pdv{\phi}{t}+\div(\vec{u}\phi)}\abs{V}
\]

\end_inset

in which
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\abs{V}:=\int_{V}1\dd{V}\qquad\ev{\cdots}:=\frac{1}{\abs{V}}\int_{V}\cdots\dd{V}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Similarly, if 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{u}\in C^{1}(V)$
\end_inset

, then 
\begin_inset Formula $\div{\vec{u}}$
\end_inset

 exists every where and
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\DDt{\abs{V}}=\oint_{V}\dd{V}=\ev{\div{\vec{u}}}\abs{V}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Shrink 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

 to an infinitesimal body, the variation of the integrand with respect to
 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{x}$
\end_inset

 can be ignored, which leads to
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{aligned}\DDt{\phi\abs{V}} & \doteq\left(\pdv{\phi}{t}+\div(\vec{u}\phi)\right)\abs{V}\\
\DDt{\abs{V}} & \doteq\left(\div{\vec{u}}\right)\abs{V}
\end{aligned}
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\doteq$
\end_inset

 means the equation is hold when 
\begin_inset Formula $\abs{V}\to0$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 is also 
\begin_inset Formula $C^{1}$
\end_inset

 smooth for 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{x}$
\end_inset

, then we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\div(\vec{u}\phi)=\phi\div\vec{u}+\vec{u}\cdot\grad{\phi}
\]

\end_inset

which leads to
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\DDt{\phi\abs{V}}-\phi\DDt{\abs{V}}\doteq\left(\pdv{\phi}{t}+\vec{u}\cdot\grad{\phi}\right)\abs{V}\label{eq:DDtOnPhiTimesV}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

It is then natural to 
\emph on
denote
\emph default
 the parenthesized quantity in the RHS as
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\boxed{\DDt{\phi}=\pdv{\phi}{t}+\vec{u}\cdot\grad{\phi}}\label{eq:DDtAtPoint}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

which is taken as the 
\emph on
definition
\emph default
 of the 
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

