\begin_layout Standard
The conservation law of energy is the alias of the 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand nameref
reference "sec:Law1ofThermodynamics"

\end_inset

.
 When applied to a control volume, it can be written as
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{aligned}\DDt{}\int_{V}\left(e+\abs{\vec{u}}^{2}/2\right)\rho\dd{V} & =\int_{V}j\dd{V}-\oint_{\partial V}\vec{n}\cdot\vec{q}\dd{S}\\
 & +\int_{V}\vec{b}\cdot\vec{u}\dd{V}+\oint_{\partial V}\vec{n}\cdot\left(\Tensor{\sigma}\cdot\vec{u}\right)\dd{S}
\end{aligned}
\]

\end_inset

in which, 
\begin_inset CommandInset nomenclature
LatexCommand nomenclature
symbol "$j$"
description "rate of heat generation per unit volume"
literal "true"

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

 is the rate of heat generation per unit volume.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Again, if we take 
\begin_inset Formula $\Tensor{\sigma}=-p\Tensor{1}+\Tensor{\tau}$
\end_inset

 into account, the formula for the law then becomes
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\begin{aligned} & \DDt{}\int_{V}\left(e+\abs{\vec{u}}^{2}/2\right)\rho\dd{V}+\oint_{\partial V}\vec{n}\cdotp\vec{u}\dd{S}\\
= & \int_{V}\left(\vec{b}\cdot\vec{u}+j\right)\dd{V}+\oint_{\partial V}\vec{n}\cdot\left(\Tensor{\tau}\cdot\vec{u}-\vec{q}\right)\dd{S}
\end{aligned}
\label{eq:ConservationOfEnergyWithDDt}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
